# CivicOS AI Handoff Protocol

Chats are temporary. Project memory is permanent.

Before starting any CivicOS work, read in order:

1. `docs/PROJECT_MEMORY.md`
2. `docs/AI_HANDOFF.md`
3. `docs/FEATURE_TRACKER.md`
4. Latest file in `docs/SESSION_LOGS/`
5. Relevant `docs/DECISIONS/ADR_*.md`
6. `docs/STYLES.md` (mandatory for any UI work)
7. `guide.md` (current scope + day plan)

After completing work, update:

- `docs/AI_HANDOFF.md` (save state)
- `docs/PROJECT_MEMORY.md` (compressed status)
- `docs/FEATURE_TRACKER.md` (if features changed)
- New `docs/SESSION_LOGS/session_NNN.md` (session summary)
- ADRs for any major technical decision

Product scope follows `guide.md`. Do not expand into full platform features unless explicitly requested.
